						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Pāṇḍya Māṟañchaḍaiyaṉ (Varaguṇa I). Year 4 = 772 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Vaṭṭeḻttu. The mahāsabhā of Vaikundavaḷanāḍu, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya</hi> in Nāṭṭāṟṟuppōkku sold land freed from taxes, to one Pañchavan Brahmādhairājan alias Chēndan Chāttan of Nellittōḻ in Malaināḍu, who donated it for food offerings in the temple of Kuṟuṅguḍi. </p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIV, No. 19.]</p>						

						</summary>
